Booting directly to the command line
<p>
To stop Kodi launching automatically on boot and launch a terminal login instead, run the following commands:
<pre>sudo systemctl disable mediacenter</pre>
<pre>sudo systemctl enable getty@tty1</pre>
</p>
<p>
After a reboot, the system will boot directly to a terminal login.
</p>
<h2>Reverting these changes</h2>
<p>
To revert these changes, run the following commands:
<pre>sudo systemctl enable mediacenter</pre>
<pre>sudo systemctl disable getty@tty1</pre>
</p>
After a reboot, the system will launch Kodi automatically.
